----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                             OpenC2X
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When OpenC2X source is organised in the tree structure like this:
.
├── build
└── src
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    ├── cam
    ├── common
    ├── dcc
    ├── denm
    ├── denmApp
    ├── gps
    ├── httpServer
    ├── ldm
    └── obd2

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                      Set up the environment
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal and run the following command

    $ sudo apt-get install libzmq3-dev libboost-all-dev protobuf-compiler libprotobuf-dev \
libgps-dev gpsd gpsd-clients libnl-3-200 libnl-3-dev libnl-genl-3-200 libnl-genl-3-dev sqlite3 \
libsqlite3-dev tmux asn1c build-essential cmake doxygen

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                      Generate source from asn
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal, navigate to asn1 folder in common:

    $ cd /path_to_my_project/src/common/asn1/
    $ ./generate.sh

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                         Without Eclipse
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal, navigate to your project root folder and configure the project:

    $ cd /path_to_my_project/build
    $ cmake ../src
    $ make all

The executables can be found in corresponding module folders found in build/binaries/

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                           With Eclipse   
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal, navigate to your project root folder and configure the project:

    $ cd /path_to_my_project/build
    $ cmake -G "Eclipse CDT4 - Unix Makefiles" ../src


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                      Importing into Eclipse
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Launch Eclipse CDT and select File > Import.
2) In the list select General > Existing Projects into Workspace and then next.
3) Browse (Select root directory) to the root folder of the project and select the build folder (in
   the example case, /path_to_my_project/build).
4) Click Finish.

